on keeping a unified germany in nato something the soviet union 
strongly opposes and bush said they talked about an expanded 
role for the western alliance in the future 
we also agree that the soviets have understandable interests in 
all of this but we did not try to fashion some compromise at this 
juncture he said in the rose garden where he and kohl took 
questions from reporters 
