the usbacked government has devalued 
the national currency for the 11th time in six weeks in advance of a 
regional summit where nicaragua will appeal for economic cooperation 
the official ratio of nicaraguan cordobas to us dollars rose 
from 1700001 to 1850001 with fridays action gas prices also 
increased by 14 cents a gallon 
on the eve of the devaluation and price hikes presidential 
spokesman danilo lacayo said the economy will be the main subject of 
the central american summit scheduled for june 15 in guatemala 
democracy will be established in the same measure that 
economically strong countries give central america the chance of 
pulling ahead he said in comments broadcast on national radio 
social and economic development benefits peace in the region 
lacayo said the administration of violeta barrios de chamorro has 
contributed its share to bringing peace to the region he pointed to 
both the plan to disband the contra rebels and reduce the size of 
the army 
the advent of mrs chamorros government to power six weeks ago 
brought hopes for an end to the countrys nineyearold civil war 
the usbacked contras had battled the leftist sandinista 
government which was defeated in february elections 
the dismantling of the contra army which was suspended several 
times has picked up steam since rebel leaders and mrs chamorros 
administration signed an accord on may 30 
it calls for the rebels to surrender their weapons by june 10 it 
also stipulates the creation of regional development centers for 
disarmed rebels which they can police on their own 
as of thursday 6842 rebels had disarmed in seven security zones 
nationwide said an official of the un peacekeeping mission for 
central america 
however contra leaders have estimated the size of their force at 
13000 
in addition mrs chamorro is studying a plan to trim the 
sandinista peoples army the president is expected to announce the 
final plan sunday 
nicaragua hopes to promote peace and economic development with 
the help of 300 million in emergency aid approved by the us 
congress last month and 120 million promised during a conference of 
donor countries in rome on thursday 
the donor countries also promised nicaragua 180 million more for 
1991 
participants in the summit will be nicaragua el salvador costa 
rica honduras and guatemala 
