<TEXT>
rita swan knows the pain of losing a child 
for deliberate denial of medical attention now she is determined 
that other parents be prosecuted for making the same decision 
work from her home in this tiny northwest iowa town ms swan 
takes credit for prompting more than two dozen prosecutions against 
parents whose children died as they followed religious teachings for 
treating illness with prayer 
most of the parents are members of christian science church so 
at one time was ms swan 
the right of a child to live should be the highest priority of 
a civilized society she said 
the christian scientists say the death of a child is one of the 
great mysteries of the ages but i say the death is not mysterious 
at all it is the logical and inevitable result of withholding 
medical attention 
rita and doug swan a math teacher at a nearby college formed 
the group childrens health care is a legal duty or child in 1983 
six years after their son matthew died of meningitis at 15 months 
ms swan 46 said there are 300 child members in 42 states and 
canada who monitor cases 
in the 80s 29 sets of prosecutions were filed for 
religiousbased medical neglect she said thats an amazing 
turnaround in general in the 70s these children just died and 
nobody cared 
the results are mixed with verdicts ranging from acquittal to 
conviction on a charge of murder 
the general counsel for the national counsel against health fraud 
said ms swan singlehandedly has raised the question of medical 
neglect with prosecutors across the country 
she puts a bug in their ears said michael botts of kansas 
city mo shes the one who deserves the credit its her guts 
that did it without her nothing would have been done 
he said several courts have ruled that parents can be held 
accountable for the death of a child notwithstanding religious 
beliefs 
youve got parents playing abraham out there they believe if 
their religion is strong enough the child will be saved its 
nothing short of human sacrifice to prove the strength of religious 
convictions he said 
other courts have dismissed such actions however based on 
religious exemptions in state child abuse laws 
christian scientists say healingbyprayer is usually successful 
and protected by guarantees of religious freedom 
we all grieved over her son but she has now used it to wage a 
vendetta against the church said wendell deware a christian 
scientist practitioner from davenport 
a small number of children in the care of christian science 
practitioners do die deware said but we encounter such 
situations so rarely 
the media has concentrated so much on these failures they will 
not take into account the vast majority of successes 
the church founded in 1879 by mary baker eddy believes that 
physical disease like sin can be healed by spiritual means alone 
there are about 2600 christian science churches in 68 countries 
most states including iowa prohibit the filing of childabuse 
charges against parents who use prayer in treatment of their 
children but prosecutors have filed other charges in several 
jurisdictions 
the swans then living in a suburb of detroit sued the church 
after matthew died in 1977 the us supreme court without comment 
let stand a lower court ruling that barred the lawsuit on religious 
freedom grounds 
he died of meningitis the common and most treatable form 
ms swan said he had three terrible fevers about a month apart 
preceding this illness each time we called a christian scientist 
practitioner and he got well based on ignorance we thought the 
practitioner had accomplished something significant 
a fourth fever claimed the boys life 
ms swan said she is driven by my sense of duty to our son to 
seek prosecutions in other cases 
im proudest of the prosecutions i think thats my strongest 
weapon against the church its not vindictiveness its something 
that has got to change i feel our work has almost singlehandedly 
turned the country around on this issue to the point where the death 
of a christian science child will almost certainly get some 
scrutiny 
