burmese territory the powerful trafficker is known to have a 
network of legal and illicit operations in thailand 
the thais have a small core of dedicated antinarcotics officers 
and have done a laudable job in stopping the production of opium 
from which heroin is refined on their own territory through crop 
substitution programs 
but thailand remains the main transit country for heroin from 
burma and laos where the opium harvests this year are expected by 
the us state department to total 2600 tons us officials say at 
least 40 percent to 50 percent of the heroin imported into the 
united states originates in the triangle 
in recent weeks local newspapers have reported that chatichai 
may offer to step up the war against drugs in exchange for american 
leniency on trade and intellectual property issues washintgon has 
threatened to further penalize thailand under us trade laws if 
greater action isnt taken to stop the piracy of american 
copyrights patents and trademarks 
thailand is regarded as one of the worst offenders in asia 
unlicensed copies of hollywood videotapes walt disney clothing 
lines american computer software and other products are openly sold 
in thailand american pharmaceutical products are similarly pirated 
six us senators last week criticized the seeming lack of 
commitment by the thai government 
american businessmen are losing scores of millions of dollars 
per year because thai laws to prevent piracy are inadequate and are 
not enforced said a letter from the senators addressed to the 
thai ambassador in washington 
thailand is already on the us trade representatives priority 
watch list for its failure to protect intellectual property 
rights and last year washington began to deny dutyfree benefits 
for about 165 million of thai imports 
the issue is regarded as a serious one in thailand because the 
united states is the countrys most important export market last 
year the thais enjoyed a 14 billion trade surplus on exports to 
the united states 
the 68yearold chatichai has been an army general diplomat 
successful businessman and veteran politician holding numerous 
cabinet posts in past governments although a generally popular and 
democratically elected figure chatichais government has been 
accused by opposition parties of massive corruption 
