friday presented a subpoena to minnesota commerce commissioner tom 
borman about durenberger loans from the commercial state bank of st 
paul 
in february the newspaper reported that durenberger received 
nearly 1 million in loans from the bank during the past decade no 
collateral was required for 21 loans during that period and six were 
offered at unusually low interest rates 
durenberger and bank officers have denied any impropriety 
the loan issue would not be raised at the senate hearings unless 
