<TEXT>
memo to donald trump 
maybe the repo men havent taken the trump princess maybe your 
checkcashing agency hasnt accused you of turning paper to rubber 
but its clear that youve fallen on hard times your name has not 
been affixed to any new edifice sporting event or species in a 
week maybe two 
you havent asked for any advice perhaps you are too humble but 
that hasnt prevented experts and some nonexperts from passing 
along a few suggestions on how to deal with your personal crisis 
your cash crisis your image crisis 
attorney marvin mitchelson says that if he were sitting in your 
financial house hed pull the window shades 
its a good time to lower the profile a little and let things 
work themselves out a bit says the celebrated celebrity divorce 
lawyer and with your spare time he suggests some leisure reading 
id reread the book trump the art of the deal 
victor kiam the guy who plugs his own razors in television 
commercials feels sympathy for a fellow entrepreneur who must take 
very unsatisfying steps but he is encouraging if you rebound 
your fall will be forgotten 
i would just keep hanging tough says quarterback doug 
flutie who was paid about 4 million to play one season with the 
trumpowned new jersey generals of the nowdefunct united states 
football league 
hes a great negotiator so id negotiate to the hilt says 
bob woolf who negotiated the deal for flutie 
i would just as hes doing sit with my bankers and try and 
restructure my debt said abraham wallach senior vice president 
of first capital management ltd a new yorkbased real estate firm 
david peterson a vice president of the american collectors 
association a minneapolisbased trade group of more than 3500 bill 
collection agencies passes along some advice more commonly given to 
more common people 
if you have trouble paying your bills you need to tell your 
creditors that youre having a problem set up a repayment plan and 
stick to it 
not everyone is eager to advise you entertainer and fellow 
casino owner merv griffin you remember how you boasted of getting 
the better of him in trading casinos the struggling resorts 
international for the taj mahal said through a publicist i 
dont comment or talk about other peoples problems 
financial analyst marvin roffman fired under pressure from trump 
after he said the taj was a bad deal would change the trump style 
of management you dont embarrass people he says 
you dont go around badmouthing your spouse or your 
executives i think thats the kind of actions that are bad for the 
morale of everybody there 
mitchelson has a few words to say about your separation from 
ivana its no crime to go through a divorce or separation 
robert kavesh a professor of finance and economics at the stern 
school of business at new york university says hold your head up 
proudly and ps prepare to sell your assets 
i think on balance trump has taken a bad rap kavesh said 
theres that mixture of envy and resentment thats frequently 
lodged against a successful person the fact is in most of his 
dealings hes been quite clean and above board 
but james grant author of grants interest rate observer and 
a prominent critic of debtfinanced wheeling and dealing offers a 
plan of action 
if i were donald trump i would sue ivana for divorce and get a 
25 million settlement with that id put everything down on the 
new york state lottery and win i think thats the most sensible 
thing he says 
</TEXT>
