<TEXT>
people who spent two years trying to 
lower their weight fat cholesterol and blood pressure celebrated 
the end of the wellness program on saturday with a healthy brunch 
the private project to improve rural americans cardiovascular 
health resulted in an average 86pound loss of body fat as well as 
reduced cholesterol and blood pressure organizers said 
about 300 people gathered for the farewell meal of a lean turkey 
sandwich oat bran muffins fruit smoked salmon and asparagus 
results of a final health screening done late last month showed 
that the 517 people who were in the program from start to finish saw 
their cholesterol drop from 2204 to 2084 an average of 54 
percent according to program director bill reger 
average blood pressures fell from 1315 over 813 to 1262 over 
783 reger said a blood pressure of 120 over 80 is considered 
ideal according to the national heart lung and blood institute 
participants also lost an average of 35 pounds in total weight 
and 86 pounds of body fat according to organizers 
the media used to call us fat city said reger now they 
recognize that were the state of the art of wellness 
study participants were encouraged to follow a lowfat 
highfiber diet exercise and use stressmanagement techniques free 
cooking and aerobics classes were offered along with lectures on 
heart disease nutrition and weight loss 
clinics also were offered to help smokers kick the habit 
