crimes have been committed by both sides over the centuries as 
transylvania a region rich in fertile land and minerals repeatedly 
changed hands it now makes up more than onethird of romania 
the indifference of past rulers to legitimate aspirations of the 
other nationality generated a deep enmity between the communities 
